# Website Logo No-Frame

Applies when placing the brand `Logo` (`website/src/app/ui/components/Logo.tsx`) anywhere in `website/`.

## Rule

`Logo` renders a bare `Image`. Consumers MUST NOT wrap it in a pill/frame ‚Äî no `br` (border), no `bg` (background fill), no `p` (padding), no `crn={999}` container, no `shd` around it. Render the `Logo` element directly, with alignment only (`as_fs` / `as_c` / direct placement in a flex row).

## Size via preset only

The logo is sized exclusively by the `preset` prop, backed by `LOGO_SIZES`:

| Preset | Size | Consumer |
|---|---|---|
| `header` | `11rem √ó 3.25rem` | `Header` main brand slot |
| `drawer` | `13rem √ó 3.85rem` | `Drawer` hero identity zone |
| `footer` | `11rem √ó 3.25rem` | `Footer` brand slot |
| `hero` | `27rem √ó 7.95rem` | `Error` centered hero card |

Do not override `w`/`h` at the call site. Add a new preset in `LOGO_SIZES` when a new size context appears (e.g. a landing hero), preserving the ~3.4:1 aspect ratio.

## Why

A border/background/padding pill around the logo adds visual weight that competes with the mark, shrinks the effective logo area, and creates inconsistent "framed vs bare" treatments across header/footer/drawer/error. The brand reads strongest as a bare mark sized to its context.

## Canonical cases

- `Header.tsx` main variant: `{isMain && resolvedBrandSlot}` ‚Äî direct render in the trailing row.
- `Footer.tsx`: `<Box as_fs>{resolvedBrandSlot}</Box>` ‚Äî alignment only.
- `Drawer.tsx` hero zone: `<Box as_fs>{resolvedBrandSlot}</Box>` ‚Äî alignment only.
- `Error.tsx`: `<Box as_c><Logo preset="hero"/></Box>` ‚Äî alignment only.

## Forbidden

- Wrapping `Logo` in a `Box` with `br` + `bg` + `p` + `crn={999}` (the removed pill pattern).
- Passing `w`/`h` props to `Logo` instead of selecting/adding a preset.
- Re-introducing a per-consumer frame "to make the logo stand out" ‚Äî enlarge the preset instead.

